1
00:00:06,490 --> 00:00:09,124
Uh-oh, she's
got that bounce.

2
00:00:09,193 --> 00:00:10,626
Do I need to call HR?

3
00:00:10,694 --> 00:00:14,129
No, I mean the bounce of a cop
who just put away a bad guy.

4
00:00:14,198 --> 00:00:16,198
After a hell of a long day
in court.

5
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:18,066
Detectives?
Got a lady here

6
00:00:18,135 --> 00:00:19,535
saying she needs
to report a murder.

7
00:00:20,571 --> 00:00:23,005
All right. Thanks, Meyers.

8
00:00:26,644 --> 00:00:27,943
DANNY:
Detective Reagan,

9
00:00:28,012 --> 00:00:30,178
my partner Detective Baez.

10
00:00:30,247 --> 00:00:31,280
And you are?

11
00:00:31,348 --> 00:00:32,814
Uh, Roxy Smith.

12
00:00:32,883 --> 00:00:34,182
So who got murdered,
Ms. Smith?

13
00:00:34,251 --> 00:00:36,018
I don't know.

14
00:00:36,086 --> 00:00:37,352
I-I mean, they
haven't been yet,

15
00:00:37,421 --> 00:00:39,354
I don't think.

16
00:00:39,423 --> 00:00:41,123
Sorry, all this
has me creeped out.

17
00:00:41,191 --> 00:00:42,858
And us confused.

18
00:00:42,926 --> 00:00:47,162
I tend bar at a place
on Avenue B, The Clasp.

19
00:00:47,231 --> 00:00:48,697
Last night,
I overheard

20
00:00:48,766 --> 00:00:50,699
one of our regulars, Joe,

21
00:00:50,768 --> 00:00:53,302
saying he'd pay
to have someone killed.

22
00:00:53,370 --> 00:00:54,703
Like, serious money.

23
00:00:54,772 --> 00:00:56,538
I'm familiar
with The Clasp.

24
00:00:56,607 --> 00:00:59,408
It's half barflies, half
college students, all drunk.

25
00:00:59,476 --> 00:01:01,643
Including all of the bartenders.

26
00:01:01,712 --> 00:01:03,645
Okay.

27
00:01:03,714 --> 00:01:05,247
I had a couple shots.

28
00:01:05,316 --> 00:01:06,548
Mm.
And if we know anything,

29
00:01:06,617 --> 00:01:09,318
it's that drunk people say
drunk things.

30
00:01:09,386 --> 00:01:10,852
But this Joe guy's
sick in the head.

31
00:01:10,921 --> 00:01:12,321
And a crap tipper.

32
00:01:12,389 --> 00:01:14,022
Not that that matters.

33
00:01:14,091 --> 00:01:15,991
Apparently, it does.
Look,

34
00:01:16,060 --> 00:01:17,900
people who hurt other people
should be stopped.

35
00:01:19,797 --> 00:01:21,797
Sit tight.

36
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:26,268
I don't know. This
whole thing seems thin.

37
00:01:26,337 --> 00:01:27,869
Yea-- (exhales)

38
00:01:27,938 --> 00:01:30,739
You know, the second collar
I ever had in my career

39
00:01:30,808 --> 00:01:33,008
was a guy
named Frank Blake.

40
00:01:33,077 --> 00:01:35,210
Did security
at The Clasp.

41
00:01:35,279 --> 00:01:36,678
He, uh, threw out
some kids.

42
00:01:36,747 --> 00:01:38,613
One of them mouthed off.

43
00:01:38,682 --> 00:01:39,948
He snapped.

44
00:01:40,017 --> 00:01:41,883
Jammed a pool cue
into the kid's eye.

45
00:01:41,952 --> 00:01:44,553
Killed him on the spot.

46
00:01:44,621 --> 00:01:47,622
So, what does
that mean?

47
00:01:47,691 --> 00:01:50,459
Means I'm gonna
have to, uh...

48
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:53,729
make another appearance.

49
00:01:59,603 --> 00:02:00,769
You know,

50
00:02:00,838 --> 00:02:02,704
it's called "quitting time"
for a reason.

51
00:02:02,773 --> 00:02:05,107
Great. Thanks.
I'll see you tomorrow.

52
00:02:05,175 --> 00:02:07,175
Come on. Four nights in a row?

53
00:02:07,244 --> 00:02:09,745
Even the bad guys
sleep sometimes.

54
00:02:09,813 --> 00:02:12,414
And yet cases still don't
magically get themselves ready

55
00:02:12,483 --> 00:02:13,615
for court.

56
00:02:13,684 --> 00:02:15,050
Anything I
can help with?

57
00:02:16,086 --> 00:02:17,619
Yeah.

58
00:02:17,688 --> 00:02:20,222
Explain to me again
why we hired Alice Dornan

59
00:02:20,290 --> 00:02:22,124
as our psychiatric consultant.

60
00:02:22,192 --> 00:02:23,458
'Cause she's a
top-notch shrink.

61
00:02:23,527 --> 00:02:24,593
Who's now saying

62
00:02:24,661 --> 00:02:25,727
that Martina Volo,

63
00:02:25,796 --> 00:02:27,273
the nanny that abused
that little girl,

64
00:02:27,297 --> 00:02:29,765
is not competent to stand trial.

65
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:30,899
Well, maybe she's right.

66
00:02:30,968 --> 00:02:33,368
Or maybe she's the one
who's out of her mind.

67
00:02:33,437 --> 00:02:35,570
Why? Because you don't like
her diagnosis?

68
00:02:35,639 --> 00:02:38,173
Martina Volo
is competent and guilty--

69
00:02:38,242 --> 00:02:40,308
no ifs, ands or buts about it.

70
00:02:40,377 --> 00:02:43,578
Look, I'm the last guy
to defend an insanity plea,

71
00:02:43,647 --> 00:02:46,581
but Dornan's got scads
of forensic experience

72
00:02:46,650 --> 00:02:50,585
and knows a lot more about
this stuff than me or you.

73
00:02:50,654 --> 00:02:53,255
Fine. Then call her and tell her
to be here tomorrow

74
00:02:53,323 --> 00:02:54,990
at 10:00 a.m. sharp.

75
00:02:55,058 --> 00:02:57,259
Erin, it's late.
She's not in.

76
00:02:57,327 --> 00:02:58,560
Then leave a message.

77
00:02:58,629 --> 00:03:00,896
Because I want to hear
this expert opinion of hers

78
00:03:00,964 --> 00:03:02,330
in person.

79
00:03:13,644 --> 00:03:16,111
Where-where are you going?

80
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:17,479
Where you just said.

81
00:03:17,548 --> 00:03:19,080
You just missed the turn.

82
00:03:19,149 --> 00:03:20,482
Traffic that way sucks.

83
00:03:20,551 --> 00:03:22,751
Westbound lanes are
under construction.

84
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:25,020
So you're Google Maps now?

85
00:03:26,323 --> 00:03:30,459
I do have some experience
with streets in this sector.

86
00:03:30,527 --> 00:03:32,672
And when you're my driver,
you go the way I tell you to.

87
00:03:32,696 --> 00:03:33,696
You got it?

88
00:03:34,731 --> 00:03:36,932
Course.

89
00:03:41,605 --> 00:03:44,473
So, what house were you in
before you came to the 2-9?

90
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:47,409
Also when driving me...

91
00:03:47,478 --> 00:03:50,312
quiet is better.

92
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:02,858
There he is.

93
00:04:02,926 --> 00:04:05,227
Mr. Mayor-Elect.

94
00:04:05,295 --> 00:04:07,195
Just "Peter," Commissioner.

95
00:04:07,264 --> 00:04:08,730
Then just "Frank."

96
00:04:08,799 --> 00:04:10,799
Please.

97
00:04:12,135 --> 00:04:15,804
Congratulations
on your election.

98
00:04:15,873 --> 00:04:17,305
Thank you.

99
00:04:17,374 --> 00:04:20,308
I got to say, none
of the mayors I served under

100
00:04:20,377 --> 00:04:22,644
got the kind of margin you got.

101
00:04:22,713 --> 00:04:26,047
Meaning, does he think
he has a mandate?

102
00:04:26,116 --> 00:04:28,783
Just a fact.

103
00:04:28,852 --> 00:04:31,753
I think we ran a smart campaign.

104
00:04:31,822 --> 00:04:34,756
But it'd be dumb to take
the credit for a tidal change.

105
00:04:34,825 --> 00:04:36,358
I just caught the wave.

106
00:04:36,426 --> 00:04:38,727
Here we are.

107
00:04:39,763 --> 00:04:42,664
And where is that?

108
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,967
Word is you don't enter a room

109
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:48,069
without knowing
why you've been invited.

110
00:04:49,106 --> 00:04:52,908
I heard rumors
you want me to stay on.

111
00:04:52,976 --> 00:04:54,709
I do.

112
00:04:54,778 --> 00:04:56,645
When I like
what somebody's doing,

113
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:58,246
I want 'em to keep doing it.

114
00:04:58,315 --> 00:05:00,415
(chuckles)
And when you don't?

115
00:05:00,484 --> 00:05:02,017
You and I
will talk.

116
00:05:02,085 --> 00:05:04,953
Not through channels,
not through the press.

117
00:05:06,256 --> 00:05:10,625
Bucking a City Hall tradition
that goes way back.

118
00:05:10,694 --> 00:05:13,895
I had sit-downs
with all the former mayors.

119
00:05:13,964 --> 00:05:16,498
Mayor Poole told me a story--

120
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:19,367
you taking him on a ride-along,
Mm.

121
00:05:19,436 --> 00:05:21,536
pointing out guys
clearly packing weapons

122
00:05:21,605 --> 00:05:24,072
who you couldn't bust
on account of his policies.

123
00:05:25,208 --> 00:05:29,077
I think it brought him conflict
at the time.

124
00:05:29,146 --> 00:05:32,480
I walked away thinking
that's just plain wrong.

125
00:05:32,549 --> 00:05:37,319
I want the NYPD to reinstate
Stop, Question and Frisk.

126
00:05:37,387 --> 00:05:39,788
Hey, at least
you got the term right.

127
00:05:39,856 --> 00:05:41,756
That hardly ever happens.

128
00:05:41,825 --> 00:05:44,326
Homework.

129
00:05:44,394 --> 00:05:46,328
We...

130
00:05:46,396 --> 00:05:48,997
still employ a version of that.

131
00:05:49,066 --> 00:05:50,332
A watered-down one.

132
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:53,001
Bring it back to 100 proof.

133
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:56,137
There's also a law on the books
that's been dry-docked,

134
00:05:56,206 --> 00:05:57,739
332.10.

135
00:05:57,808 --> 00:05:58,974
Vagrancy enforcement.

136
00:05:59,042 --> 00:06:01,943
Tourism's a $44 billion
business in this city.

137
00:06:02,012 --> 00:06:07,148
But not if Tex, Sven and Hideki
are afraid to leave the hotel.

138
00:06:07,217 --> 00:06:09,851
And put the homeless where?

139
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:13,254
I'll redirect funding
to more shelters.

140
00:06:13,323 --> 00:06:16,825
You hit the ground running.

141
00:06:16,893 --> 00:06:20,295
(chuckles): There's
a lot of ground to cover.

142
00:06:20,364 --> 00:06:23,164
(grunts softly)

143
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:25,233
So,

144
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:27,235
what's the ask?

145
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:30,839
Word is you never enter a room
without one.

146
00:06:32,843 --> 00:06:35,510
I want you to make
a personnel change.

147
00:06:35,579 --> 00:06:37,379
I have a couple
of recommendations

148
00:06:37,447 --> 00:06:40,649
for your new DCPI.

149
00:06:43,487 --> 00:06:47,689
Garrett Moore
is supremely fit for the job.

150
00:06:47,758 --> 00:06:49,557
He's smart, quick on his feet,

151
00:06:49,626 --> 00:06:53,161
well-liked by the press
and all the city agencies.

152
00:06:53,230 --> 00:06:55,563
And that is a bad thing how?

153
00:06:55,632 --> 00:06:57,699
He needs to be liked.

154
00:06:57,768 --> 00:06:59,634
He basks in being liked.

155
00:06:59,703 --> 00:07:01,036
He's a Labrador retriever,

156
00:07:01,104 --> 00:07:02,837
and you're gonna need
a pit bull.

157
00:07:02,906 --> 00:07:05,807
I want to take
this city back,

158
00:07:05,876 --> 00:07:07,809
and your guys are my Marines.

159
00:07:07,878 --> 00:07:11,212
There's gonna be pushback
that Garrett's gonna cave under.

160
00:07:11,281 --> 00:07:12,347
And you know I'm right,

161
00:07:12,416 --> 00:07:14,716
as sure as you're sitting here.

162
